refsect2.programlisting:
void
cairo_append_path (cairo_t *cr,
                   const cairo_path_t *path);

refsect2.para:
This function gives the arc in the direction of increasing angles;
see cairo_arc_negative() to get the arc in the direction of
decreasing angles.

informalexample.programlisting:
cairo_save (cr);
cairo_translate (cr, x + width / 2., y + height / 2.);
cairo_scale (cr, width / 2., height / 2.);
cairo_arc (cr, 0., 0., 1., 0., 2 * M_PI);
cairo_restore (cr);

refsect2.para:
Adds a cubic BÃ©zier spline to the path from the current point to
position (x3
, y3
) in user-space coordinates, using (x1
, y1
) and
(x2
, y2
) as the control points. After this call the current point
will be (x3
, y3
